quran[30]{c,v,t}:
  89,1,"By the dawn,"
  89,2,"and the ten nights,"
  89,3,"and the even and the odd,"
  89,4,"and by the night when it departs."
  89,5,"Is there in this an oath for one endowed with understanding?",footnotes:182697:1
  89,6,"Have you not seen how your Lord dealt with Ad",footnotes:182698:1
  89,7,"of Iram, known for their lofty columns,",footnotes:182699:1
  89,8,"the like of whom no nation was ever created in the lands of the world?",footnotes:182700:1
  89,9,"And how did He deal with Thamud who hewed out rocks in the valley?",footnotes:182701:1
  89,10,"And with Pharaoh of the tent pegs",footnotes:182702:1
  89,11,"who transgressed in the countries of the world"
  89,12,"spreading in them much corruption?"
  89,13,"Then their Lord unloosed upon them the lash of chastisement."
  89,14,"Truly your Lord is ever watchful.",footnotes:182703:1
  89,15,"As for man, when his Lord tests him by exalting him and bestowing His bounties upon him, he says: “My Lord has exalted me.”",footnotes:182704:1
  89,16,"But when He tests him by straitening his sustenance, he says: “My Lord has humiliated me.”",footnotes:182705:1
  89,17,"But no; you do not treat the orphan honourably,",footnotes:182706:1|182707:2
  89,18,"and do not urge one another to feed the poor,",footnotes:182708:1
  89,19,"and greedily devour the entire inheritance,",footnotes:182709:1
  89,20,"and love the riches, loving them ardently.",footnotes:182710:1
  89,21,"But no; when the earth is ground to powder,",footnotes:182711:1
  89,22,"and when your Lord appears with rows upon rows of angels,",footnotes:182712:1
  89,23,"and when Hell is brought near that Day. On that Day will man understand, but of what avail will that understanding be?",footnotes:182713:1
  89,24,"He will say: “Would that I had sent ahead what would be of avail for this life of mine!”"
  89,25,"Then on that Day Allah will chastise as none other can chastise;"
  89,26,"and Allah will bind as none other can bind."
  89,27,"(On the other hand it will be said): “O serene soul!",footnotes:182714:1
  89,28,"Return to your Lord well-pleased (with your blissful destination), well-pleasing (to your Lord).",footnotes:182715:1
  89,29,"So enter among My (righteous) servants"
  89,30,"and enter My Paradise.”"
